$200 off first months rent! Full lawn service and mobile friendly, In-Home Security system INCLUDED. Tenant pays for Electricity, Gas, water, sewer, internet and trash service. 600+ credit score required.  Very spacious 3 bedroom, 2 full bathroom home with bathtubs. Full lawn service and mobile friendly, In-Home Security system, INCLUDED. $200 off the first months rent. 600+ Credit score required, no Section 8. Tenant responsible for utilities. The lease term is 12 months.  The owners live in the other side of the duplex, so it really has a home feel, not just another duplex. The property is well cared for. The duplex faces a line of single family homes, not other duplexes.  It is un-furnished.  Bedrooms and bathrooms:  There are three bedrooms and two bathrooms. Both bathrooms have shower/bathtub combo. The master bedroom has a large walk-in closet. Both upstairs bedrooms have closets as well.  Look and feel:  There are two large Bradford Pear trees out front for shade. You walk in to a very spacious living room with a tall ceiling and hardwood floor. The living room leads to an open dining area and kitchen. The kitchen has a tile floor and the bedrooms have new carpet. The downstairs bathroom got new floor and paint, to give it a more modern feel. The owners live in the other side of the duplex so maintenance and aesthetics are kept up, easily.  Appliances:  There are currently side-by-side washer and drier. They can be removed if needed. Air Conditioning and Heating are central air. There is a Vivint security system that is active when Internet is activated. Front door is keypad activated, for key-less entry. Security system can be operated by cell phone app. There is a doorbell camera that is accessible via cell phone app, through the security system. There is a single car garage.   Parking:  There is a single car garage. The driveway easily accommodates two vehicles. Depending on how vehicles are parked, a third can also be parked.   Pets:  There is an $800 pet fee if pets are authorized. Full non-refundable pet fee due at lease signing, in addition to all other deposits. Perspective pets must be under 25 pounds to be considered. No pets under three years old.   Square footage and floor plan: 1,128 square feet. Master bedroom and full bathroom downstairs. Two bedrooms upstairs. Full bathroom upstairs.  Outdoor space:  There is a concrete pad in fenced-in back yard. The sidewalk is connected to the driveway so walking and bicycling to other areas is very convenient.  Security:  6" tall fenced-in back yard with lockable gate, Vivint modern security system with doorbell camera and mobile access. Owners live in the other side of the duplex.  Neighborhood:  Conveniently located within a half mile from Moser's Grocery store, Auburn Hills Park, Derby Ridge Elementary School, Missouri Credit Union, Taco Bell, Central Bank, McDonald's, Skyzone and Commerce Bank. Within a mile is Lang Middle School, Jimmy John's, La Siesta, Wilson's Garden Center, Columbia's Finest Child Day Care, Smiley Lane Family Medicine Clinic, Rangeline Carwash, Agave, Gumby's Pizza, Sonic, Arena Liquor and Landmark Bank.

As you walk into this available, spacious duplex, you'll notice the open floor plan with a large carpeted living room that flows into a nice sized, dining room and a widely spaced kitchen, both with linoleum flooring.  The kitchen already houses the standard appliances and has plenty of drawer and cabinet space.  As you walk through the kitchen, you'll come to a nice sized, secluded laundry room with washer/dryer hookups.  The two bedrooms, both located in the back of this duplex unit, are positioned on separate sides of the central connecting hallway.  The master bedroom has its own closet as well as a full-sized bathroom. The second bedroom, while also spacious, does not have a connecting bathroom, but does have a good-sized closet. This 1350 square foot house sits in quiet convenient south central Springfield with easy access to everywhere you want to go. This charming neighborhood has mature trees and many newly remodeled homes with character. This property at 1951 S. Virginia Ave is no exception. Perfect for a young family, business professional or empty nesters looking to downsize, this home has two bedrooms plus a bonus room and one large bathroom. The master bedroom has three closets! This house has been completely remodeled and it's next tenants will be the first to enjoy these brand new upgrades. No surface was left untouched from new carpets to new paint from walls to ceiling. The kitchen and bathroom have been remodeled with new energy saving components like a Choice Flow toilet, Frigidaire stainless steel refrigerator, and Kenmore washer and dryer combo included. The kitchen has a large walk in pantry with more storage space than you can use. Say goodbye to high energy bills! This house is loaded with money saving features. The furnace and central air conditioner are high efficiency units less than one year old. The home was remodeled on the outside as well with modern insulation, siding and new windows. The attic had heavy insulation blown in when the new heat and a/c units were added, perfect for comfortable living without the pain of huge energy bills. Outside both the front and fenced back yard offer shade from colorful trees surrounding the property. If you are moving from an apartment, get used to driving into your automatic garage with added storage and leaving home from your warm car in the morning without scraping snow and ice.
